Create a new rails app

  $ rails new (PROJECT NAME)
  $ rails new pinteresting 

Run rails server from within project, so it knows which application to run that server for.

	$ cd pinteresting
  $ rails server 
  $ rails s
  $ ctrl + c

Setup git 

  $ git config --global user.name "MY NAME"
  $ git config --global user.email "MY EMAIL"

  To check:

    $ git config --global user.name
    $ git config --global user.email

Initialize git in project

  $ git init
  $ git status

Get rid of .DS_STORE .gitignore file - I guess rails automatically doesn't have .DS_STORE

Commit changes

  $ git add .
  $ git commit -am "Create initial repo"

  -a flag helps keep track of deleted files
